{"article_id":"LQU2Qwd5hmMQxLyM","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Department of Justice","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"( DOJ )","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"on Monday announced","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"that it is siding with a district court ruling","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"that found the Affordable Care Act unconstitutional .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The move is an escalation of the Trump administration 's legal battle against the health care law .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"The DOJ previously argued in court","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that the law 's pre-existing condition protections should be struck down .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Now , the administration argues","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"the entire law should be invalidated .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"U.S. District Judge Reed O'Connor ruled in December","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that the Affordable Care Act 's individual mandate is unconstitutional","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"and that the rest of law is therefore invalid .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"The DOJ said Monday","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"that it agrees","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"the decision should stand","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"as the case works its way through the appeals process in the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 5th Circuit .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"`` The Department of Justice has determined","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"that the district court ' s judgment should be affirmed , ''","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"the department said in a short letter to the appeals court .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"The move is certain to prompt new denunciations from Democrats ,","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"who had already seized on the Trump administration 's earlier call","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"for the pre-existing condition protections to be struck down .","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"That stance was a major issue in last year 's midterm elections ,","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"and many Republican candidates in tough races struggled with whether to say","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"they agreed with the Trump administration 's position .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"Many legal experts in both parties think","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"the lawsuit ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"which was brought by 20 GOP-led states ,","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"will not ultimately succeed .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"The district judge","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"who ruled against the law in December","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"is known as a staunch conservative .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"The case centers on the argument","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"that","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"since Congress repealed the tax penalty in the law 's mandate","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"for everyone to have insurance in 2017 ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"the mandate can no longer be ruled constitutional under Congress 's power","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"to tax .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"The challengers then argue","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"that all of ObamaCare should be invalidated","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"because the mandate is unconstitutional .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"Most legal experts say","depth":4},{"id":43,"text":"legal precedent shows","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"even if the mandate is ruled unconstitutional ,","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"the rest of ObamaCare should remain unharmed ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"as that is what Congress voted to do in the 2017 tax law","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"that repealed the mandate 's penalty .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"Justin Wise contributed to this report ,","depth":2},{"id":50,"text":"which was updated on March 26 at 5:50 a.m .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":101,"left":99,"right":100,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":83,"right":98,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":83,"left":70,"right":82,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":70,"left":56,